post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A legalization of all drugs may lead to many [replacing](https://theintercept.com/2018/04/20/marijuana-legalization-alcohol-consumption/) part of their alcohol consumption with healthier drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Creativity can be stimulated through the use of drugs. Drugs could help us to live in a more creative dynamic society.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various currently illegal drugs have valuable medical properties; these substances may have the potential to solve problems in our society such as mental health issues. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Laws should be introduced on an entirely pragmatic basis, not on the basis of moral signaling. If legalising drugs reduces harm, this should be sufficient evidence that it is a good policy. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will be seen as a sign of the government/authority giving up on protecting people from the harm they could do, to themselves and others, through poorly selected drug use.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, in the USA, there is a [pharmaceutical opioid crisis](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/us-opioid-epidemic). Drug companies and legal policies cannot be trusted to protect citizens. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research chemicals, which are used as [date rape drugs](https://drugabuse.com/date-rape-drugs/), are constantly evolving and changing formulations to escape existing regulation. It is unlikely that the law would be able to control all of them. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Mexico](https://www.globalresearch.ca/destabilizing-mexico/12707) has been destabilized by drug cartel activities such as lawlessness, kidnappings, increasing corruption and frequent assassinations.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Prohibition clearly isn't enough either, and all but ensures that honest education and information becomes impossible, making it exaggerated and ineffective."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Ending the war on drugs will reduce [police casualties](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Driving a car or operating machinery while under the influence of drugs is illegal. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drugs being illegal deters many people from using them. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If government regulations lead to drugs being expensive, it is possible people will still try to access cheaper drugs on a black market and these drugs may still be dangerous or of poor quality. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Controlled substances, while controlled, are still obtained through the black market. Whether it is a date-rape drug or marijuana, legislation still cannot control whether illegal drugs are illegally obtained. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Individuals who seek out "forbidden" activities will still seek that thrill and choose other illegal and possibly more dangerous activities to participate in. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drugs are already easily accessible and quite expensive yet the alcohol industry is still flourishing. It doesn't have to be one or the other. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The negative repercussions of drug use should be prosecuted on their own merit and context \\(without prosecuting the drug use itself\\).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This essentially places the onus of care back on the government to regulate to keep users safe. If the idea is the government should not control what we do with our bodies this proposition does not really make sense.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drug users will encourage other people, who do not know how to handle drugs and/or aren't smart and/or mature enough to try it. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It can also cause users to mix alcohol with other drugs, which [endangers users' health](https://www.northpointwashington.com/blog/dangers-mixing-alcohol-drugs/) even more."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[In German law](http://www.emcdda.europa.eu/countries/drug-reports/2018/germany/drug-laws-and-drug-law-offences_en), the use of drugs is not mentioned as a legal offense.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Science can already study drugs, just with some [constraints](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4307971/). I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[In German law](http://www.emcdda.europa.eu/countries/drug-reports/2018/germany/drug-laws-and-drug-law-offences_en), the use of drugs is not mentioned as a legal offense.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Smoking](https://www.cancer.org/cancer/cancer-causes/tobacco-and-cancer/secondhand-smoke.html) puts the drugs into the air, meaning non-consenting people take the drug as well.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's not a given that the low well-being of drug users' families are a result of the drug use. The confounding variable is likely mental health issues. It's possible \\(and sometimes preferable\\) to solve the mental health issues, while not stopping the drug use."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has only permitted research which [supports their agenda](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/08/18/feds-limit-research-marijuana-medical-use/31547557/) of prohibition. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This does not take into account plants that do not grow well everywhere. For these cases, there is still a reliance on other communities that fall under different legislation to cultivate the plants. This keeps a connection with the international criminal drug trade.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The risk of unknown purity and poor-quality drugs will be minimized. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having drugs be both illegal and valuable has funded extensive infrastructure for smuggling things across the US border.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The evidence suggests that criminalisation does not significantly decrease drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "But we don't make moral judgements all the time every day. We all need to stop thinking clearly and rationally every now and then, for activities including but not limited to play, fun, pleasure, love, chilling out, taking a load off… So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A legalization of all drugs may lead to many [replacing](https://theintercept.com/2018/04/20/marijuana-legalization-alcohol-consumption/) part of their alcohol consumption with healthier drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help reduce social rifts.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Becoming involved with drugs is going to become harder for children because they will be denied access to the legal market and there will be drastically less demand, and thus supply and availability for black market drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legal sellers will be highly scrutinized and won't want to risk losing their license. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Knowledge that a friend or relative is using drugs can cause significant psychological stress to a caring or sensitive individual.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The number of deaths from overdose will rise dramatically as a result of easy access to drugs including meth, MDMA, and heroin. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Ending the war on drugs will reduce [police casualties](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drugs being illegal deters many people from using them. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs have a long history of responsible use within their historical context.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Once you replace the dealers and kingpins of the neighborhoods whose flashy lifestyle would look appealing to naive kids, drugs would lose some of their appeal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an appeal to nature fallacy. Nature is not the word on what ought to be done with its products.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a [correlation](https://americanaddictioncenters.org/rehab-guide/addiction-and-violence) between drug use and \\(violent\\) crime.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The logic of this argument would necessitate prohibition of alcohol, along with cigarettes, prescription painkillers, household cleaning products, motor vehicles, power tools; and anything a person may use to end their life consciously or accidentally. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A large portion of the public is irresponsible. Giving everyone the opportunity to use \\(or abuse\\) drugs would have negative consequences on these individuals.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug cartels will not cease their activities if drugs are legalised. They will simply move to other areas to keep their profits \\(drugs for children, black market drugs, human trafficking\\). So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The responsible use of drugs for recreational purposes does not harm others and therefore can not be considered immoral. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'They would have died on those drugs whether or not they were legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The effects of different drugs play a role in the daily spending habits of drug users; thus more commonplace usage may change people's spending patterns in a way that negatively affects the economy."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking the stigma and secrecy away from drug taking would mean family and friends would notice drug abuse earlier and be able to intervene.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This essentially places the onus of care back on the government to regulate to keep users safe. If the idea is the government should not control what we do with our bodies this proposition does not really make sense.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'People may drive under the influence of drugs or make other decisions with public consequences.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'That is not an effect of drugs. It can be argued that the neglect of children living with addicted parents is caused by the lack of welfare and safety net, and its effect can probably be lessened if addictions are treated as a healthcare problem. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under legalisation, self-injection as a route of administration may be reduced, as safer alternatives become available.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Incarceration](https://beckleyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/paper_07.pdf) of drug offenders is expensive and a burden on taxpayers.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cannabis-derived approved drugs containing \\(half-synthetic\\) THC or CBD [can be researched](https://accpjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/phar.1187) as an alternative to cannabis.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'True freedom of choice means that individuals must face the consequences of their actions, whether they are good or bad. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The right to bodily integrity protects individuals from [forced labor, slavery or torture](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodily_integrity).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is [no/little research](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/drugfacts/hallucinogens) regarding the long-term effects of hallucinogens. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Using a fake ID in a legal establishment implies much more work and risk than just buying from the unregulated black market.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Individuals who seek out "forbidden" activities will still seek that thrill and choose other illegal and possibly more dangerous activities to participate in. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation of drugs allows for them to be regulated by the state and sold directly to the consumer, increasing purity. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Colorado, between 2014 and 2017, [over $500 million](https://money.cnn.com/2017/07/19/news/colorado-marijuana-tax-revenue/index.html) in government revenue was raised by taxes and fees on marijuana sales. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Government finances from drug legalization have the potential to fund for social welfare if a proper distribution of taxation is ensured.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of this emotional harm is directly caused by erroneous negative perceptions of drug use like the ones being perpetrated here. Many people are unfairly vilified for responsibly using drugs, simply because they are illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies might just as well synthesize new, less addictive and harmful drugs to meet the demand.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It would likely be 'cooler' because companies can market the drugs like they do with cigarettes and alcohol."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without proper education, people who are more prone to drug addiction may be more likely to get addicted to a drug.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar compound will always exist.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This isn't possible with the most popular date rape drug alcohol, at least not in higher doses, as it's taste is quite unmistakable."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Psychosis](https://www.earlypsychosis.ca/pages/curious/concerned-safety) can cause the sufferer to carry out self-harm or, in severe cases, suicide. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It will create jobs, not only in distribution but also in drug clinics and counseling centers. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If a government wanted to put money into harm reduction, it could do so without legalising drugs in order to avoid the costs of enforcing a drug prohibition. It could instead cut other government programs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is little medical discrimination for those who use legal harmful substances such as alcohol or tobacco.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A legalization of all drugs may lead to many [replacing](https://theintercept.com/2018/04/20/marijuana-legalization-alcohol-consumption/) part of their alcohol consumption with healthier drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research shows that education has helped the [decrease](https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/03/26/cigarette-smoking-decline_n_6855468.html) in number of tobacco smokers. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prohibition of drugs at no time endangers the personal autonomy of the individual.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The evidence suggests that criminalisation does not significantly decrease drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The use of psychoactive substances](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3202501/) has been a part of human culture for thousands of years; drugs have been used for religious, medical or recreational purposes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow for effective tools and strategies to fight criminal organizations.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Profit for companies" is better than "profit for criminal cartels", if those are the two choices.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalization of recreational drug use is not necessary for legalization of expanded drug research. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
